cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SI, cs.HC 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with predicting human trajectories in crowded spaces using recurrent neural networks. It also involves learning from visual data and evaluating the model on pedestrian datasets. The paper also involves machine learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a new LSTM model for trajectory prediction. Robotics (cs.RO) is another likely sub-category as the model can be used for robot navigation in crowded spaces. Social and Information Sciences (cs.SI) is also a possible sub-category as the model can be used to study human behavior in crowded spaces. Finally, Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) is another possible sub-category as the model can be used to design better interfaces for human-robot interaction in crowded spaces.
